'''Morita no Kami''' (守宅神, also read as Moriya no Kami, Moritaku no Kami, or Morita no Kami<ref name="yamadamoriya"/>) is a deity from the folk traditions of the {{ill|Suwa Region|lt=Suwa Region|lt=Suwa region|ja|諏訪地方|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa region|qq=}} in Nagano Prefecture, central to the {{ill|Suwa faith|ja|諏訪信仰|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa faith|qq=}}. Also known as '''守田ノ神'''<ref name="moriya">{{Cite book|和書|year=2017|title=神長官守矢史料館のしおり|edition=第三版|page=11|editor=茅野市神長官守矢史料館|editor-link=神長官守矢史料館|chapter=守矢氏系譜}}</ref> or '''Moriya no Kami'''<ref name="nobukawa">延川和彦「信濃国官社諏訪神社神長官守矢家略系図」『[https://dl.ndl.go.jp/info:ndljp/pid/927368/21 諏訪氏系図 続編]』飯田好太郎、1921st year 、21頁。</ref>, he is said to have been worshiped as a god of hunting and mountains.

== Overview ==
[[File:Moriya Family Tree - 守矢氏系図.png|170px|thumb|{{center|Genealogy of the Moriya clan showing the first five generations from Moreya to Chikato.}}]]
